    "body": "@saltegg1986 \r\n> Thank you very much for your answer.\r\n> I have set the difficulty in my genesis block,. At the beginning, the time of the block generation is short, but after a while, the time will turn longer. So is there a way to save the time of thg block generation.\r\n\r\nfor geth version 1.8.13: `sed -i 's/return CalcDifficulty(chain.Config(), time, parent)/return big.NewInt(2)/' /go/go-ethereum/consensus/ethash/consensus.go`\r\n\r\nthis will permanently fix the difficulty to a constant, just change `2` to whatever you desire.",
